extends layout.pug

block content
    h1.content-title
        i.material-icons feedback
        | Tooltip
    article.box
        .box-body
            h2 Basic
            p You can add tooltips to any element you like. Just add a #[code tooltip] class to it, and by default the title will be used as the message.
            br
            .text-center
                button.btn-success.tooltip(title='This is a nice tooltip') Hover me
            br
            hr
            h2 Custom message
            p If you need to use the element's title for another purpose, and want a custom message for the tooltip, you can override it with the #[code data-tooltip] attribute.
            br
            .text-center
                button.btn-danger.tooltip(title='This title will not appear in the tooltip' data-tooltip='This is the tooltip message') Hover me
            br
            hr
            h2 Placement
            p You can change the default placement of the tooltip (top) with the classes #[code tooltip-left], #[code tooltip-right] and #[code tooltip-bottom].
            br
            .text-center
                button.btn-warning.tooltip(title='This is a nice tooltip') Default
                button.btn-warning.tooltip.tooltip-left(title='This is a nice tooltip') Left
                button.btn-warning.tooltip.tooltip-right(title='This is a nice tooltip') Right
                button.btn-warning.tooltip.tooltip-bottom(title='This is a nice tooltip') Bottom
            br
            hr
            h2 Limit Alignment
            p By default, the tooltip is aligned at the start (top or left) limit of the trigger. You can change this by using the class #[code tooltip-end], so the tooltip will be aligned at the end (bottom or right) limit of the trigger.
            br
            .text-center
                h3 Top
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-start(title='This is a nice tooltip') Start
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip(title='This is a nice tooltip') Center
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-end(title='This is a nice tooltip') End
            br
            .text-center
                h3 Left
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-left.tooltip-start(title='This is a nice tooltip') Start
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-left(title='This is a nice tooltip') Center
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-left.tooltip-end(title='This is a nice tooltip') End
            br
            .text-center
                h3 Right
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-right.tooltip-start(title='This is a nice tooltip') Start
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-right(title='This is a nice tooltip') Center
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-right.tooltip-end(title='This is a nice tooltip') End
            br
            .text-center
                h3 Bottom
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-bottom.tooltip-start(title='This is a nice tooltip') Start
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-bottom(title='This is a nice tooltip') Center
                button.btn-primary.tooltip.tooltip-bottom.tooltip-end(title='This is a nice tooltip') End
            br